  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased production by members, improved marketing and financial sustainability</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Partnership between IDRA and Agriterra started in 2010. After shift in Agriterra&#x2019;s approach of having a business advisor based in Zambia, he conducted an organisation assessment to better understand the performance and proposed way forward of the partnership. The organization assessment report is available in which joint activities and objectives have been elaborated.

Activities in action plan:

1.1 Improved service provision structure to members; action plan available plus financial projections1.2 Continuation of 20 demonstration plots 1.3 Provide extension services that are financially sustainable, by ensuring that members who receive extension services market their rice through IDRA2.1 Governance Training2.2 Elaborate new IDRA Strategic Plan incl. marketing plan and financial forecast to become more financially independent.2.3 Enhance financial sustainability of IDRA through internal capitalisation and paid membership services; show added value of IDRA to realize a higher percentage of paid-up members2.4 Improve business plan SINZA Women&#x2019;s Association2.5 Member meeting to explain what services IDRA provides to its members (and what not)2.6 Facilitation of monthly board meetings3.2 3.1 In-house Basic financial management training &#x2013;3.3 Financial management / governance training for SACCOs4.1 Workshop Record keeping and services for members (together with CDRA)

Increased production by members, improved marketing and financial sustainability for IDRA.</narrative>
  </description>
